  "title": "RoboTTT: Context Scaling for Robot Policies",
  "summary": "RoboTTT uses test-time training to compress up to 8,000 visuomotor timesteps into fast weights without increasing inference latency with context length. The reported real-robot gains suggest execution history can become adaptive model state, though the evaluation covers controlled manipulation tasks.",
